race.comment: BEATTY (1) was very impressive on debut here a fortnight ago and is clearly the one to beat on the back of that effort. He rises in weight, but this looks to shape very similarly to his last start. Can lob just off the speed and get over the top of them to remain unbeaten. CONSIGNMENT (3) won a recent trial which a few of his rivals came through. He did so in good fashion there at Belmont and he maps for a lovely run under Parnham. Can put his best foot forward on debut. MYSTIC SMILE (11) has a few handy siblings who have been tried at Group and Listed level, the most recent of those being Street Band. Chris Parnham hops in the saddle for her debut today and she beat CONSIGNMENT in a 400m here back in October. Expecting a sharp debut. HILLSIDE AVENUE (9) is a half-sister to the old champ Valour Road. Has shown some ability at the trials and is worth keeping safe. ROGUE RULER (7) is next best.
